[@ closeDiv() @]*
The average rate of change is [_______]{$aroc3} feet per second. 


---


### Estimating the instantaneous rate of change: the ball's velocity

As the length of the duration gets smaller and smaller, the average rate of change becomes a better and better estimate of the instantaneous rate of change.  In this case, the average velocity over a very small period of time [`t \in [ [$t0], [$t1] ]`] helps us estimate the ball's velocity at time [`t = [$t0]`].

[@ openDiv({ "class" => "promptOrInstruction" }) @]*
Based on the above results, along with using even smaller values of [`\Delta t`], make an educated guess what the instantaneous
velocity of the ball is when [`t_0 =[$t0]`] seconds.  
[@ closeDiv() @]*

  

The instantaneous rate of change is [____]{$iroc} feet per second.  

